   member_body="GE"
   resolution="TBD">
   <issue_management
    owner="Tom Hendrix"
    priority="low"
    category="Document"/>
<description>
 <p>
   <b>SC4 part number:</b>  </p>
 <p>
   <b>(2) Clause:</b> 10303-1121 4.2.1 Document
 </p>
 <p>
   <b>(3) Paragraph:</b> 
 </p>
 <p>
   <b>(5) Comment:</b>
 </p>
 <p>
It is not clear if a Document can be referenced by Product_versions which are not Document_versions.</p>
 <p>
   <b>(6) Proposal:</b>
 </p>
 <p>
Add a rule to ensure that every Product_version, referencing the Document is a Document_version.</p>
 </description>

<comment
   by="Rob Bodington"
   date="04-09-23">
<description>
PLCS agrees with the proposal and passes the comment onto the PDM modules team
</description>
</comment>

<comment
   by="Tom Hendrix"
   date="04-10-15">
<description>
RULE product_version_constraint FOR
    (Product_version);
WHERE
 WR1: SIZEOF ( QUERY ( pv &lt;* Product_version | ( NOT (
     'Document_and_version_identification_arm.'+ 'Document_version' IN TYPEOF ( pv)
     ) ) AND ( 'Document_and_version_identification_arm.Document'+
     'Document' IN TYPEOF ( ts.of_product) ) ) ) ) =0;
END_RULE;

</description>
</comment>
</issue>


